This paper discusses the concept of fairness in machine learning models, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also touches on issues related to ethics and privacy (cs.CY), as well as security and cryptography (cs.CR) in the context of machine learning. Finally, the paper draws on existing work in moral and political philosophy (cs.ET) to inform the discussion on fairness in machine learning.
